      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Engines\" title=\"Engines\">Engines</a> * Gosu</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg/330px-Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg/500px-Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3b/Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Korean_musician-Pansori_gosu-01.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pansori\">Pansori</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pansori_gosu\">Gosu</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Gosu</b>,<br />\na <a href=\"/Chess_Engine_Communication_Protocol\" title=\"Chess Engine Communication Protocol\">Chess Engine Communication Protocol</a> compatible chess engine by <a href=\"/Arkadiusz_Paterek\" title=\"Arkadiusz Paterek\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a>, originated as a part of his masters thesis. In <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_language\">Korean</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gosu\">its name</a> means expert or master. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Tournament_Play\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Tournament Play</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2004\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2004</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2005\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2006_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2006 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Chess_Engine\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Engine</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Misc\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Misc</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In Arkadiusz Paterek's  paper <i>Modeling of an evaluation function in games</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, referring his thesis  <i>Modeling of an evaluation function in chess</i>, the <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> is mentioned using a <a href=\"/Neural_Networks#Perceptron\" title=\"Neural Networks\">single-layer perceptron</a> design inspired by <a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro's</a> <a href=\"/Michael_Buro#GLEM\" title=\"Michael Buro\">general linear evaluation model</a> (GLEM) <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> in the domain of <a href=\"/Othello\" title=\"Othello\">Othello</a>. Gosu performs <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning#LogisticRegression\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">logistic regression</a> to optimize weights of corresponding features aka minimize the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mean_squared_error\">mean squared error</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loss_function\">loss function</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_descent\">gradient descent</a> over a set of 6.2 million quiet positions from master games. For each position, it squares the difference of an <a href=\"/Oracle\" title=\"Oracle\">oracle</a> score from the outcome of the game, of 0.999 for a win, 0.5 for a draw, 0.0013 for a loss, and the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dot_product\">dot product</a> of the weight and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Feature_(machine_learning)\">feature vector</a>, squashed by a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_function\">logistic function</a> into a 0.0 to 1.0 range of a <a href=\"/Pawn_Advantage,_Win_Percentage,_and_Elo\" title=\"Pawn Advantage, Win Percentage, and Elo\">winning probability</a>. To speed up matters after <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">tuning</a>, an <a href=\"/Evaluation_Hash_Table\" title=\"Evaluation Hash Table\">evaluation cache</a> is used along with <a href=\"/Lazy_Evaluation\" title=\"Lazy Evaluation\">lazy evaluation</a>, which performed well in Gosu's <a href=\"/MTD(f)\" title=\"MTD(f)\">MTD(f)</a> framework.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tournament_Play\">Tournament Play</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Tournament Play\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Gosu played four <a href=\"/Polish_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"Polish Computer Chess Championship\">Polish Computer Chess Championships</a>, after a strong debut at the <a href=\"/PCCC_2004\" title=\"PCCC 2004\">PCCC 2004</a>, it won the <a href=\"/PCCC_2005\" title=\"PCCC 2005\">PCCC 2005</a>, and became third at the <a href=\"/PCCC_2006\" title=\"PCCC 2006\">PCCC 2006</a> and played the <a href=\"/IOPCCC_2007\" title=\"IOPCCC 2007\">IOPCCC 2007</a> where it lost the final rounds versus later winner <a href=\"/Glaurung\" title=\"Glaurung\">Glaurung</a> and runner up <a href=\"/WildCat\" title=\"WildCat\">WildCat</a>.\nGosu further performed at the <a href=\"/CCT7\" title=\"CCT7\">CCT7</a> with 4½/8. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Arkadiusz_Paterek\" title=\"Arkadiusz Paterek\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w szachach</i>. Masters thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a> (Polish, Modeling of an evaluation function in chess)</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Arkadiusz_Paterek\" title=\"Arkadiusz Paterek\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w grach</i>. <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mimuw.edu.pl/~paterek/mfog.ps.gz\">zipped ps</a> (Polish, Modeling of an evaluation function in games)</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2004\">2004</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2004\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=18&amp;t=48925\">Gosu</a> by <a href=\"/Grzegorz_Sidorowicz\" title=\"Grzegorz Sidorowicz\">Grzegorz Sidorowicz</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, September 15, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=18&amp;t=48980\">gosu v.0.2</a> by <a href=\"/Arkadiusz_Paterek\" title=\"Arkadiusz Paterek\">Arek Paterek</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, September 20, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=127\">Gosu does not find the mate in 1...</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Dr._Axel_Schumacher&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Dr. Axel Schumacher (page does not exist)\">Dr. Axel Schumacher</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, October 03, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Checkmate\" title=\"Checkmate\">Checkmate</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005\">2005</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2005\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=409382\">Gauntlet Gosu v0.6 with games</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Karl-Heinz_S%C3%B6ntges&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Karl-Heinz Söntges (page does not exist)\">Karl-Heinz Söntges</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 04, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=420582\">Gauntlet Gosu v0.7 with clear improvement - games</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Karl-Heinz_S%C3%B6ntges&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Karl-Heinz Söntges (page does not exist)\">Karl-Heinz Söntges</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 12, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=2422\">Gosu 0.8</a> by Telmo Escobar, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, April 29, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=425209\">Gauntlet Gosu v0.8 - games</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Karl-Heinz_S%C3%B6ntges&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Karl-Heinz Söntges (page does not exist)\">Karl-Heinz Söntges</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 10, 2005</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=428984\">Gauntlet Gosu v0.9 - games - Fafis was removed</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Karl-Heinz_S%C3%B6ntges&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Karl-Heinz Söntges (page does not exist)\">Karl-Heinz Söntges</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 30, 2005</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2006_...\">2006 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2006 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=5317\">Problem with new Gosu</a> Postby Tony Thomas, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, August 05, 2006</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=5323\">Gosu loosing on time</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Volker_Pittlik&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Volker Pittlik (page does not exist)\">Volker Pittlik</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, August 06, 2006</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=25286\">Gosu 0.16 v Thor's Hammer 2.28 (queen sac)</a> by <a href=\"/Graham_Banks\" title=\"Graham Banks\">Graham Banks</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 06, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Thor%27s_Hammer\" title=\"Thor&#39;s Hammer\">Thor's Hammer</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Engine\">Chess Engine</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Engine\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://kirr.homeunix.org/chess/engines/Norbert&#39;s%20collection/Gosu%20(Compilation)/\">Index of /chess/engines/Norbert's collection/Gosu (Compilation)</a> by <a href=\"/Norbert_Raimund_Leisner\" title=\"Norbert Raimund Leisner\">Norbert Raimund Leisner</a>, hosted by <a href=\"/Kirill_Kryukov\" title=\"Kirill Kryukov\">Kirill Kryukov</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Misc\">Misc</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Misc\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gosu\">Gosu from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gosu_%28disambiguation%29\">Gosu (disambiguation) from Wikipedia</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gosu_%28programming_language%29\">Gosu (programming language) from Wikipedia</a></dd></dl>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Gosu&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pansori_gosu\">Pansori gosu from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Arkadiusz_Paterek\" title=\"Arkadiusz Paterek\">Arkadiusz Paterek</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Modelowanie funkcji oceniającej w grach</i>. <a href=\"/University_of_Warsaw\" title=\"University of Warsaw\">University of Warsaw</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mimuw.edu.pl/~paterek/mfog.ps.gz\">zipped ps</a> (Polish, Modeling of an evaluation function in games)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Michael_Buro\" title=\"Michael Buro\">Michael Buro</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/3-540-48957-6_8\">From Simple Features to Sophisticated Evaluation Functions</a></i>. <a href=\"/CG_1998\" title=\"CG 1998\">CG 1998</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://skatgame.net/mburo/ps/glem.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Engines\" title=\"Engines\">Up one Level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228125135\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.107 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.693 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 89/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 162/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache